{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida8000454-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s706"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"706"},"text":"§ 706.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Administration of leave required to be taken","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8000455-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s706/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A period of leave required to be taken under section 876a or 1182(c)(2) of this title shall be charged against any accrued leave to the member’s credit on the day before the day such leave begins unless the member elects to be paid for such accrued leave under subsection (b). If the member does not elect to be paid for such accrued leave under subsection (b), or does not have sufficient accrued leave to his credit to cover the total period of leave required to be taken, the leave not covered by accrued leave shall be charged as excess leave. If the member elects to be paid for accrued leave under subsection (b), the total period of leave required to be taken shall be charged as excess leave.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8000456-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s706/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8000457-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s706/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A member who is required to take leave under section 876a or 1182(c)(2) of this title and who has accrued leave to his credit on the day before the day such leave begins may elect to be paid for such accrued leave. Any such payment shall be based on the rate of basic pay to which the member was entitled on the day before the day such leave began. If the member does not elect to be paid for such accrued leave, the member is entitled to pay and allowances during the period of accrued leave required to be taken.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida8000458-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s706/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in paragraph (1) and in sections 707 and 707a of this title, a member may not accrue or receive pay or allowances during a period of leave required to be taken under section 876a or 1182(c)(2) of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida8000459-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s706/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A member required to take leave under section 876a or 1182(c)(2) of this title is not entitled to any right or benefit under chapter 43 of title 38 solely because of employment during the period of such leave.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida800045a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/81/s2/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–81, § 2(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-11-20"},"text":"Nov. 20, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1085"},"text":"95 Stat. 1085","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/568/tV/s506/c/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–568, title V, § 506(c)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4341"},"text":"106 Stat. 4341","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tX/s1070/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title X, § 1070(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2859"},"text":"108 Stat. 2859","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/353/s2/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–353, § 2(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3169"},"text":"108 Stat. 3169","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/dA/tXV/s1503/a/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, div. A, title XV, § 1503(a)(7)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-02-10"},"text":"Feb. 10, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/511"},"text":"110 Stat. 511","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [[div. A]","children":[],"tail":", title X, § 1087(a)(4)], "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1654"},"text":"114 Stat. 1654","children":[],"tail":", 1654A–290; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/dA/tV/s506/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, div. A, title V, § 506(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-02"},"text":"Dec. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2535"},"text":"116 Stat. 2535","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida800045b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida800045c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida800045d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/s506/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, § 506(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “pending review of certain court-martial convictions” at end of section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/s506/c/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, § 506(c)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or 1182(c)(2)” after “section 876a”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/s506/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, § 506(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or 1182(c)(2)” after “section 876a” in pars. (1) and (2) and substituted “sections 707 and 707a” for “section 707” in par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/s506/c/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, § 506(c)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or 1182(c)(2)” after “section 876a”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398","children":[],"tail":" struck out “(1)” before “A member required” and struck out par. (2) which read as follows: “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s974"},"text":"Section 974 of this title","children":[],"tail":" does not apply to a member required to take leave under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s876a"},"text":"section 876a of this title","children":[],"tail":" during the period of such leave.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106","children":[],"tail":" substituted “chapter 43 of title 38” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s4301"},"text":"section 4301 of title 38","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/353"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–353","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of par. (1) by substituting “chapter 43” for “section 4321”, could not be executed because intervening amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":" had substituted “section 4301” for “section 4321”. See below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":" substituted “4301” for “4321”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/568"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–568","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 4321” for “section 2021”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida800045e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida800045f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1994 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/353"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–353","children":[],"tail":" effective with respect to reemployments initiated on or after the first day after the 60-day period beginning "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", with transition rules, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/353/s8"},"text":"section 8 of Pub. L. 103–353","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s4301"},"text":"section 4301 of Title 38","children":[],"tail":", Veterans’ Benefits."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"ida8000460-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/81/s7"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–81, § 7","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-11-20"},"text":"Nov. 20, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1089"},"text":"95 Stat. 1089","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/209/s12/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–209, § 12(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-12-06"},"text":"Dec. 6, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/1407"},"text":"97 Stat. 1407","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/98/209/s12/b"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amendments made by this Act [enacting this section and sections 707 and 876a of this title and amending sections 701, 813, 832, 838, 867, and 869 of this title] shall take effect at the end of the sixty-day period beginning on the date of the enactment of this Act.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The amendments made by section 2 [enacting this section and sections 707 and 876a of this title and amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s701"},"text":"section 701 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall apply to each member whose sentence by court-martial is approved on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-01-20"},"text":"January 20, 1982","children":[],"tail":"—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" under section 864 or 865 (article 64 or 65) of title 10, United States Code, by the officer exercising general court-martial jurisdiction under the provisions of such section as it existed on the day before the effective date of the Military Justice Act of 1983 [see Effective Date of 1983 Amendment note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s801"},"text":"section 801 of this title","children":[],"tail":"]; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" under section 860 (article 60) of title 10, United States Code, by the officer empowered to act on the sentence on or after the effective date of the Military Justice Act of 1983.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amendments made by section 3 [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s813"},"text":"section 813 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall apply to each person held as the result of a court-martial sentence announced on or after the effective date of such amendments."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amendment made by section 4(a) [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s832"},"text":"section 832 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall apply with respect to investigations under section 832 (article 32) of title 10, United States Code, that begin on or after the effective date of such amendment."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"“(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amendment made by section 4(b) [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s838"},"text":"section 838 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall apply to trials by courts-martial in which all charges are referred to trial on or after the effective date of such amendment."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"“(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amendment made by section 5 [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s867"},"text":"section 867 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall apply to any accused with respect to a Court of Military Review [now Court of Criminal Appeals] decision that is dated on or after the effective date of such amendment.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
